snippet: The claims were below expectations of economists, and a survey of manufacturing showed a rise in factory jobs.
abstract: Labor Department reports that applications for weekly unemployment benefits fell 2,000 to a seasonally adjusted 326,000, suggesting that December slowdown in job growth may have been temporary.
lead_paragraph: The claims were below expectations of economists, and a survey of manufacturing showed a rise in factory jobs.

headline.main: Labor Data Suggests Dip In December Was Outlier
headline.print_headline: Labor Data Suggests Dip In December Was Outlier
